reviews.text: Crayfish all year round, so we always visit whenever we’re here. Tasted a little frozen this time round but the sauce is still really good. Petai was a little harder and sauce wasn’t as good but not too bad.

It's extremely rare for me at award a 1-star rating to any eatery as I know F&B business is a very difficult industry in Singapore. Having said this, this place simply blows my mind. Taking their mediocre taste into consideration, this probably is the priciest Tze Char in Hougang. $10.30 for a box of salted egg dice chicken with white rice really teaches A-level student the meaning profitization.

Found a dead cockroach on the egg of my packet food. That’s disgusting and unhygienic. They only know to keep increase price and charge customers more but food taste is so average and now unclean food.
Have ordered more than 20 times, it’s my neighborhood zichar. Faves are: prawn roll, pork curry, homemade tofu. It’s really popular on weekend evenings and there’s a bit of a wait for takeaways.

Ordered in by Deliveroo. Wifes hor fun tasteless. my yang zhou fried rice is one of the worst i ever had. no wok hey for both. and my prawn is super  sticky unfresh. Didnt even give 2 packets of green chilli for this 2 items. only 1 to share between us. I think they don eat their own cooked food.  Had to use own sambal and pickles to just fill the tummy. Nvr again.
